      margin-left: auto; /* Center align */
      margin-right: auto; /* Center align */
    }
  </style>
</Fragment>

<!-- FAQs Widget ******************* -->

<FAQs
  title="Frequently Asked Questions."
  classes={{ container: 'max-w-6xl' }}
  columns={1}
  items={[
    {
      title: 'What Benefits Does the Inflation Reduction Act of 2022 Offer?',
      description:
    "The Inflation Reduction Act is a landmark legislation that aims to tackle various economic and environmental challenges. One of its key provisions is the focus on energy efficiency and clean energy production. The act allocates significant funds for energy security and climate change programs. If you are looking to make your home more energy-efficient or invest in clean energy, this act provides various tax credits and incentives to help you do so.",
    },
    {
  title: 'What is Included in the Residential Clean Energy Property Credit? (25D)',
  description:
    "The 25D tax credit covers solar panels, solar water heaters, geothermal heat pumps, small wind turbines, and fuel cells. Must be installed in your primary or second home. Covers 30% of installation costs, no upper limit.",
},
{
  title: 'How Do Electric Vehicles (EVs) Fit Into the Energy Efficiency Equation?',
  description:
    "The 30D tax credit offers up to $7,500 for a new EV, and up to $4,000 for a qualified used EV. The 30C credit provides a 30% rebate for home EV charging station installation.",
},
{
  title: 'How do I Benefit from The Energy Efficiency Home Improvement Credits?',
  description:
    "The 25C credit offers tax benefits for energy-saving home improvements like heat pumps, heat pump water heaters, insulation, energy-efficient windows, and exterior doors",
},
{
  title: 'What is the Difference Between Tax Credits and Rebates?',
  description:
    "Tax credits like 25C, 25D, and 30C reduce your tax liability. HEEHRA and 30D offer instant rebates at the time of purchase or installation.",
},
{
  title: 'Can Federal Tax Credits Be Carried Forward to the Next Tax Year?',
  description:
    "Tax credits under 25D can be carried forward to future tax years. The 25C credit is available annually but must be claimed in the same tax year the improvements are made; it cannot be rolled over."
}
  ]}
  
/>
